TLG A7\nWHITWEY\nFAIR TO PAY DEBTS\nNorth Adams Baseball Association\nPlans Entertainment.\nThe directors of the North Adams\nbaseball association voted at a meet\ning last night (Wednesday) to hold a\nweek's fair during the week of No\nvember 2S In Odd Fellows hall. The\ndesire of the directors Is to raise\nmoney to liquidate the debts of the\nassociation before and transfers of\nstock to new owners Is made. They\nare confident that they will be able\nto clean the slate before making a\nsale of any of the stock.\nNo date has been set for the meet\ning of the association as the mem\nbers are at sea over the proposed\nchanges In the by-laws calling for\neach share of stock to represent a\nvote Instead of, as Is the case now,\neach stockholder having one vote re\ngardless of the number of shares he\nowns. v\nThe proposed change Is puzzling\nmany of them and communication\nhas been opened with the proper\nstate authorities with a view to\nstraightening out the matter. When\nthis Is done the meeting will be held\nNorth Adams Herald.\nBIG LEAGUE BASE BALL\nPROGRAM\nA Western Girl's\nSacrilice\nA utiir f the wcht by the Chiiniplon Kilin\nCo, fthowliig tlm I'llliiMH'H of lilnl comimii\niitim, the UHywnril course, ilWIionor mill\nilUcnu r mid a ltrr' MU-rltU'i lliat wtvci\ntli family' honor.\nWhere the Sun Sets\nA Different Western Dram?\nHome Made Mince Pies\nA Refined Comedy by the Than\nhouser Co.\nGetting Nervous\nComedy\nEVERY NIGHT\nThe Whitney Orchestra\nSEVEN PIECES\nst\nResults of Yesterday's Games in the\nTwo Major Leagues.\nAmerican League Results.\nAt Washington (First game) Bos\nton. 5: Washington, 2; (second\ncame) Boston, 5; Washington, C\nAt Chicago Detroit, 5; Chicago,\n11.\nAt Philadelphia New York,\nPhiladelphia, 1,\nAt St. Louts Cleveland, 5;\nTxmls, 6.\nAmerican League Standing.\nW. I,.\nPhiladelphia 102\nNew York 86\nDetroit \"5\nBoston Si\nCleveland 69\nChicago C6\nWashington fifi\nSt\nOol.t MM\"\nwiour ir nourishing\nKama,\n48\n63\nfi5\n70\n80\nS4\nS